message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Lithuania in the past 5 years was the inauguration of the country's first female President, Gitanas Nausėda, in July 2019. This event marked a historic moment for Lithuania as it broke the long-standing tradition of male presidents since the country's independence in 1990. Gitanas Nausėda's election and subsequent inauguration symbolized a shift towards greater gender equality and representation in Lithuanian politics.
